Cover FX Face Products Review & Demo!

Clinique Deep Comfort Collection 
Admittedly Glasgow is having a fairly mild Winter all things considered. That doesn't mean that the central ... can result in dry skin. If like myself you have fairly sensitised and dry skin on your body and hands the Clinique Deep Comfort Collection could be just what you are looking for. Now the Clinique Deep Comfort Collection is pretty extensive so I have whittled it down to my favourite products...


No pun intended (okay ... moisturiser. If like myself you require hand creams to be fuss free, quick to absorb, non-greasy and most importantly deeply hydrating Clinique Deep Comfort Hand and Cuticle Cream is the way to go. A rich yet lightweight hand cream which is fragrance ... replenishing weekly yet small enough to pop in a handbag.


Perhaps my favourite two products from the range have to be Clinique Deep Comfort Body Wash and the coordinating body butter. Most Winters my skin seems to suffer from eczema more so ... what so ever with such brand but the products are very basic and the shower soap does nothing for me. Enter Clinique Deep Comfort Body Wash, a rich, again non-scented, creamy body wash that deeply cleanses the skin without being stripping and ... can be annoying, especially since most fragrance free body moisturisers are body lotions which I don't find all that hydrating. Clinique Deep Comfort Body Butter is the answer to my woes - thick yet quickly absorbed, super hydrating yet non-greasy and ... a long way. I may just make body moisturising a daily occurrence if it is that easy!

You can find the Clinique Deep Comfort Collection £16.50-£29 via Clinique - link.
